<paragraph blockId="17.[151,409,440,466]" box="[151,409,440,466]" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,409,440,466]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,409,440,466]" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[151,303,440,466]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Hesperiinae">Hesperiinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doherty" authorityYear="1866" box="[315,409,440,466]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Baorini">Baorini</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,510,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">
<bibRefCitation box="[151,344,510,535]" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" refString="Fan, X., Chiba, H., Huang, Z., Fei, W., Wang, M. &amp; Safian, S. (2016) Phylogenetic framework of the tribe Baorini (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae: Hesperiinae) inferred from multiple gene sequences. PLoS ONE, 11 (7), e 0156861. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0156861" type="journal article">
Fan 
<emphasis box="[202,253,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
used multiple gene sequences to clarify the phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doherty" authorityYear="1866" box="[1018,1105,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Baorini">Baorini</taxonomicName>
, which they confirmed to be monophyletic. Based on eight species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1949" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1949" box="[634,853,546,571]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[634,704,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Borbo</emphasis>
Evans, 1949
</taxonomicName>
included in their analysis, they found 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1949" box="[1299,1369,546,571]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1299,1369,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Borbo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be polyphyletic and accordingly validated the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Lee" authorityName="Lee" authorityYear="1966" box="[708,907,582,607]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pseudoborbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[708,857,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Pseudoborbo</emphasis>
Lee
</taxonomicName>
for the Asian 
<taxonomicName authority="(Moore)" authorityName="Moore" box="[1068,1271,582,607]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pseudoborbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bevani">
<emphasis box="[1068,1171,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">P. bevani</emphasis>
(Moore)
</taxonomicName>
and attempted to establish a new genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Chiba, Fan &amp; Safian" authorityName="Chiba, Fan &amp; Safian" box="[456,808,618,643]" class="Gastropoda" family="Vanikoridae" genus="Larsenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[456,556,620,643]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Larsenia</emphasis>
Chiba, Fan &amp; Sáfián
</taxonomicName>
to accommodate 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mabille)" authorityName="Mabille" box="[1017,1259,618,643]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemella">
<emphasis box="[1017,1141,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">B. gemella</emphasis>
(Mabille)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Druce)" authorityName="Druce" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perobscura">
<emphasis box="[1275,1435,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">B. perobscura</emphasis>
(Druce)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Plotz)" authorityName="Plotz" box="[300,488,654,679]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holtzi">
<emphasis box="[300,398,654,679]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">B. holtzi</emphasis>
(Plötz)
</taxonomicName>
. Unfortunately, 
<taxonomicName box="[687,787,655,678]" class="Gastropoda" family="Vanikoridae" genus="Larsenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[687,787,655,678]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Larsenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an invalid homonym as the name is preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName authority="Waren" authorityName="Waren" box="[151,335,691,715]" class="Gastropoda" family="Vanikoridae" genus="Larsenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,251,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Larsenia</emphasis>
Warén
</taxonomicName>
, a genus of marine gastropod molluscs, so the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doherty" authorityYear="1866" box="[880,964,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Baorini">Baorini</taxonomicName>
genus will need to be renamed. Further work will also be needed to allocate the remaining species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1949" box="[863,933,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[863,933,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Borbo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to their correct genera. Of the three 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1949" box="[1366,1436,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1366,1436,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Borbo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species that we reared (
<bibRefCitation author="Cock" box="[412,679,762,787]" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" refString="Cock, M. J. W. &amp; Congdon, T. C. E. (2012) Observations on the biology of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera) principally from Kenya. Part 4. Hesperiinae: Aeromachini and Baorini. Zootaxa, 3438, 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="2012">Cock &amp; Congdon 2012</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boisduval)" authorityName="Boisduval" box="[699,984,762,787]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borbonica">
<emphasis box="[699,845,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">B. borbonica</emphasis>
(Boisduval)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hopffer)" authorityName="Hopffer" baseAuthorityName="Hopffer" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[1039,1280,762,787]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fatuellus">
<emphasis box="[1039,1166,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">B. fatuellus</emphasis>
(Hopffer)
</taxonomicName>
remain in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1949" box="[222,292,798,823]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[222,292,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Borbo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hopffer)" authorityName="Hopffer" box="[348,564,798,823]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lugens">
<emphasis box="[348,451,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">B. lugens</emphasis>
(Hopffer)
</taxonomicName>
was not treated by 
<bibRefCitation box="[780,968,798,823]" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" refString="Fan, X., Chiba, H., Huang, Z., Fei, W., Wang, M. &amp; Safian, S. (2016) Phylogenetic framework of the tribe Baorini (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae: Hesperiinae) inferred from multiple gene sequences. PLoS ONE, 11 (7), e 0156861. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0156861" type="journal article">
Fan 
<emphasis box="[828,877,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
. Based on the caterpillars, we consider 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hopffer" baseAuthorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fatuellus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">B. fatuellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[302,406,834,859]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lugens">
<emphasis box="[302,406,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">B. lugens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be closely related, but the caterpillar of 
<taxonomicName box="[888,1034,834,859]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borbonica">
<emphasis box="[888,1034,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">B. borbonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the type species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1949" box="[1266,1336,834,859]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1266,1336,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Borbo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is more similar to that of 
<emphasis box="[370,509,871,895]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Afrogegenes</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Wallengren)" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1911" box="[522,802,870,895]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Apallaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="letterstedti">
<emphasis box="[522,642,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">letterstedti</emphasis>
(Wallengren)
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<emphasis box="[855,902,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">niso</emphasis>
Linnaeus auct.). 
<bibRefCitation box="[1116,1436,870,895]" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" refString="De Jong, R. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2017) A re-appraisal of Gegenes Hubner, 1819 (Lepidoptera, Hesperiidae) based on male and female genitalia, with the description of a new genus, Afrogegenes. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 160, 41 - 60. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 22119434 - 16001003" type="journal article">De Jong &amp; Coutsis (2017)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<emphasis box="[266,405,907,931]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Afrogegenes</emphasis>
for three species previously placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1819" box="[840,936,907,930]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Gegenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[840,936,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Gegenes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<emphasis box="[952,1110,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">
<taxonomicName authority="Strand, 1911" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1911" box="[952,1106,906,931]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Apallaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="letterstedti">A. letterstedti</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
A. 
<emphasis box="[1153,1266,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">hottentota</emphasis>
(Latreille) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Evans)" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1911" box="[151,329,943,967]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Apallaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocra">
<emphasis box="[151,233,943,966]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">A. ocra</emphasis>
(Evans)
</taxonomicName>
. Although 
<bibRefCitation box="[452,637,942,967]" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" refString="Fan, X., Chiba, H., Huang, Z., Fei, W., Wang, M. &amp; Safian, S. (2016) Phylogenetic framework of the tribe Baorini (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae: Hesperiinae) inferred from multiple gene sequences. PLoS ONE, 11 (7), e 0156861. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0156861" type="journal article">
Fan 
<emphasis box="[500,547,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
include 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius)" authorityName="Fabricius" box="[732,1035,942,967]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Gegenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nostrodamas">
<emphasis box="[732,906,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">G. nostrodamas</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
in their analysis, unfortunately they do not include any 
<emphasis box="[387,526,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Afrogegenes</emphasis>
spp. Based on the caterpillars, 
<emphasis box="[908,1047,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Afrogegenes</emphasis>
may be closer to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1949" box="[1271,1341,978,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1271,1341,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Borbo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1819" box="[151,247,1015,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Gegenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,247,1015,1038]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">Gegenes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. More rearing and more genetic analysis will be needed to take this further.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="488" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,510,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">
<bibRefCitation author="Cock" box="[199,478,1050,1075]" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" refString="Cock, M. J. W. &amp; Congdon, T. C. E. (2012) Observations on the biology of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera) principally from Kenya. Part 4. Hesperiinae: Aeromachini and Baorini. Zootaxa, 3438, 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="2012">Cock &amp; Congdon (2012)</bibRefCitation>
overlooked the observation by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sevastopulo" box="[832,1051,1050,1075]" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" refString="Sevastopulo, D. G. (1964) Attraction of butterflies to light. Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 18, 73 - 74." type="journal article" year="1964">Sevastopulo (1964)</bibRefCitation>
that 
<taxonomicName box="[1107,1253,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Borbo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borbonica">
<emphasis box="[1107,1253,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="488">B. borbonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be attracted to light by night. In our experience, crepuscular species may be attracted to light at dusk or dawn. In addition, many species of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Noyes" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[343,476,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hesperiidae</taxonomicName>
(and other butterfly families) are rarely attracted to lights by night, but we attribute this to individuals being disturbed and taking flight at night rather than true nocturnal behaviour.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
